                    <p>
                        With less than two months to go for the <b>Ericsson Leadership Summit 2017</b>, an event that gathered hundreds of Ericsson top managers from all over the world in Globen, the <b>Ericsson Customer Experience</b> team got a very unusual request from high up in the ladder.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        We were asked to craft a VR experience that showed how the new brand could be applied to the new media. And even though our hands were already full with the creation of an end-to-end product flow, helping in the creation of a brand reveal video and doing our presentation of the <b>Ericsson UX 2.0</b> vision, we took up the challenge anyway.
                    </p>
